{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"1qgmr670moitcxxpmnmjxlp","title":"Software Development","desc":"","updated":1657122756313,"created":1655541876900,"custom":{},"fname":"areas.software-development","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","name":"digital-garden","selfContained":true},"contentHash":"020c54894a8dfb8fe42f6f75b8a17f0f","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"areas.software-development","id":"1qgmr670moitcxxpmnmjxlp","vaultName":"digital-garden"},"value":"areas.software-development.four-types-of-documentation","alias":"areas.software-development.four-types-of-documentation","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":3,"offset":44},"end":{"line":5,"column":61,"offset":102},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"areas.software-development.four-types-of-documentation"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"areas.software-development","id":"1qgmr670moitcxxpmnmjxlp","vaultName":"digital-garden"},"value":"reference.dev.react.component-composition","alias":"React Component Composition","position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":3,"offset":703},"end":{"line":31,"column":76,"offset":776},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"reference.dev.react.component-composition"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"areas.software-development","id":"1qgmr670moitcxxpmnmjxlp","vaultName":"digital-garden"},"value":"areas.software-development.acceptance-test-four-layer-architecture","alias":"areas.software-development.acceptance-test-four-layer-architecture","position":{"start":{"line":88,"column":19,"offset":2967},"end":{"line":88,"column":89,"offset":3037},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"areas.software-development.acceptance-test-four-layer-architecture"}},{"from":{"fname":"root","vaultName":"digital-garden"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":3,"offset":409},"end":{"line":15,"column":33,"offset":439},"indent":[]},"value":"areas.software-development","alias":"areas.software-development"}],"anchors":{"software-development":{"type":"header","text":"Software Development","value":"software-development","line":8,"column":0,"depth":1},"documentation":{"type":"header","text":"Documentation","value":"documentation","line":10,"column":0,"depth":2},"topics-im-interested-in":{"type":"header","text":"Topics I'm interested in","value":"topics-im-interested-in","line":28,"column":0,"depth":2},"toolbox":{"type":"header","text":"Toolbox","value":"toolbox","line":34,"column":0,"depth":2},"frontend":{"type":"header","text":"Frontend","value":"frontend","line":36,"column":0,"depth":2},"try-out":{"type":"header","text":"Try out","value":"try-out","line":41,"column":0,"depth":2},"frontend-1":{"type":"header","text":"Frontend","value":"frontend-1","line":42,"column":0,"depth":3},"software-design":{"type":"header","text":"Software Design","value":"software-design","line":50,"column":0,"depth":2},"testing-principles":{"type":"header","text":"Testing principles","value":"testing-principles","line":60,"column":0,"depth":2},"bdd":{"type":"header","text":"BDD","value":"bdd","line":61,"column":0,"depth":3},"acceptance-tests--executable-specifications":{"type":"header","text":"Acceptance Tests / Executable Specifications","value":"acceptance-tests--executable-specifications","line":72,"column":0,"depth":3}},"children":["qhnsko8zwma7lmvkgxnnxh6","tuxfl9vy5d9c7db4ei5lsrx","hmz33wwmnmznosm3ku3u295","icwk3xi0o8ixuyks5vw11yg"],"parent":"ckpt5dqzm4fv2ysnyyqi5q7","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"software-development\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#software-development\"></a>Software Development</h1>\n<h2 id=\"documentation\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#documentation\"></a>Documentation</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"/digital-garden/notes/tuxfl9vy5d9c7db4ei5lsrx\">Four Types of Documentation</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Documentation Checklist</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>When explaining several bigger topics it's good to first list them up in the introductory text and then follow up\nwith sub-sections using the same name as title</p>\n<pre class=\"language-md\"><code class=\"language-md\">There are two formats supported:\n<span class=\"token list punctuation\">-</span> Text format (<span class=\"token code-snippet code keyword\">`.txt`</span> extension)\n<span class=\"token list punctuation\">-</span> Binary format (<span class=\"token code-snippet code keyword\">`.prof`</span> extension)\n\n<span class=\"token title important\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">##</span> Text format (`.txt` extension)</span>\n\n...\n\n<span class=\"token title important\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">##</span> Binary format (`.prof` extension)</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"topics-im-interested-in\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#topics-im-interested-in\"></a>Topics I'm interested in</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Software Design &#x26; Architecture</li>\n<li>Clean Code &#x26; maintainable human readable source code</li>\n<li>Developer productivity, automation</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"toolbox\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#toolbox\"></a>Toolbox</h2>\n<h2 id=\"frontend\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#frontend\"></a>Frontend</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/digital-garden/notes/opuu0qsqju8wp97fxlzes7t\">React Component Composition</a></li>\n<li>Use Storybook!</li>\n<li>Use Typescript!</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"try-out\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#try-out\"></a>Try out</h2>\n<h3 id=\"frontend-1\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#frontend-1\"></a>Frontend</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Testing with Storybook\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://storybook.js.org/blog/test-component-interactions-with-storybook/\">https://storybook.js.org/blog/test-component-interactions-with-storybook/</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Data Fetching libraries\n<ul>\n<li>React: React Query, RTK Query, SWR, Apollo</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Tailwind</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"software-design\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#software-design\"></a>Software Design</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Build a Ubiquitous Language (共通言語)</li>\n<li>Separate <strong>WHAT</strong> from <strong>HOW</strong></li>\n<li>Public interfaces are important!\n<ul>\n<li>They should communicate <strong>WHAT</strong> not how - in their name</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Single responsibility\n<ul>\n<li>If you cannot properly name it it probably has more than one responsibility</li>\n<li>One class - one thing</li>\n<li>One method - one thing</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"testing-principles\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#testing-principles\"></a>Testing principles</h2>\n<h3 id=\"bdd\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#bdd\"></a>BDD</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Use the domain language (The Ubiquitous Language)</li>\n<li>Drive Development with Executable Specifications</li>\n<li>Focus ond WHAT not HOW\n<ul>\n<li>Say nothing about HOW it does those things</li>\n<li>Only on WHAT it does</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Make the code simple, easily readable!</li>\n<li>Test ONE thing</li>\n<li>Start tests with \"Should do this thing\"\n<ul>\n<li>The thing you are testing is the subject</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"acceptance-tests--executable-specifications\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#acceptance-tests--executable-specifications\"></a>Acceptance Tests / Executable Specifications</h3>\n<p>Sources:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JDD5EEJgpHU\"><img src=\"/digital-garden/assets/youtube-icon.svg\" alt=\"Youtube Icon\" style=\"height:1rem;\"> Continuous Delivery - How To Write Acceptance Tests</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=knB4jBafR_M\"><img src=\"/digital-garden/assets/youtube-icon.svg\" alt=\"Youtube Icon\" style=\"height:1rem;\"> Continuous Delivery - Acceptance Testing with Executable Specifications</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Properties</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Life-like scenarios</li>\n<li>In Production like Test environments</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Executable Specifications</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Write them beforehand from the User Story</li>\n<li>It should be from the perspective of an external user of the system\n<ul>\n<li>Use the Ubiquitous language!</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Separate What the system does from how it does it\n<ul>\n<li>Imagine replacing the system with something else that fulfills the same function - the test should still make\nsense!</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Write them so clear that even the least technical person can understand it!</li>\n<li>Focus on what the user wants - link them to user stories\n<ul>\n<li>Find an underlying need, what the user wants to achieve</li>\n<li>Why are you making this change? Find that and focus on that in the acceptance test</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Have at least one test for each acceptance criteria of your user stories</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Implementation: <a href=\"/digital-garden/notes/qhnsko8zwma7lmvkgxnnxh6\">Acceptance Test Four Layer Architecture</a></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<strong>Children</strong>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"/digital-garden/notes/qhnsko8zwma7lmvkgxnnxh6\">Acceptance Test Four Layer Architecture</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/digital-garden/notes/tuxfl9vy5d9c7db4ei5lsrx\">Four Types of Documentation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/digital-garden/notes/icwk3xi0o8ixuyks5vw11yg\">Inbox</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/digital-garden/notes/hmz33wwmnmznosm3ku3u295\">Japanese Terms</a></li>\n</ol>\n<hr>\n<strong>Backlinks</strong>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/\">Home</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"w4mxpqpj9ftyo6pw17k3wj6","title":"Home","desc":"","updated":1655543408062,"created":1648806032875,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","name":"digital-garden","selfContained":true},"contentHash":"85